The Teladi Pelican is notable for its mediocrity as a freighter. It has taken to the level of an art form the capacity to be neither outstandingly good nor bad on any single metric. The single greatest mystery is why Teladi traders themselves use this ship, when there are many other more profitable options available.\n\nRecognising the commercial weakness of the Pelican, the Sentinel model boasts increased cargo space, improving the ship's overall trade run profitability.
